<persName> — Names of People
    Use for every name.
    Example: <persName ref="#ortelius">Abraham Ortelius</persName>

    Metadata may be defined in <listPerson>:

    <listPerson>
        <person xml:id="ortelius">
            <persName>Abraham Ortelius</persName>
            <sex value="male"/>
            <birth when="1527" place="#antwerp"/>
            <death when="1598" place="#antwerp"/>
            <occupation>Cartographer</occupation>
        </person>
    </listPerson>

<placeName> — Geographic Names

    Use for cities, rivers, regions, seas, mountains.
    Example: <placeName ref="#antwerp">Antwerp</placeName>

    List form:

    <listPlace>
        <place xml:id="antwerp">
            <placeName>Antwerp</placeName>
            <location><geo></geo></location>
            <country></country>
        </place>
    </listPlace>

<hi> — Typography and Emphasis

    Marks italics or other typographic shifts.
    Example: <hi rend="italic">The Theatre of the Whole World</hi>

<figure> — Maps, Ornaments, and Headings

    Used heavily for map titles, center text, and ornaments.

    <figure type="ornament">
        <head>Fleuron</head>
        <figDesc>Decorative floral ornament</figDesc>
    </figure>

<date> — Dates

    Example: <date when="1606">1606</date>

    Supports ranges:
        <date from="1500" to="1520"/>

        <date notBefore="1500" notAfter="1520"/>

<fw> — Page Furniture (Headers, Page Numbers, Catchwords)

    Running headers:
        <fw type="header" place="top">THEATRVM ORBIS TERRARVM</fw>

    Page numbers:
        <fw type="pageNum" place="top">5</fw>

    Catchwords:
        <fw type="catch" place="bottom">WORLD</fw>

<unclear> — Uncertain or Illegible Text

    Example: <unclear reason="faded" cert="low">Ortelius</unclear>

    Attributes:
        reason: faded, smudged, torn

    cert: low, medium, high

<supplied> — Missing or Supplied Text

    Example: <supplied reason="lost">ABRAHAMI</supplied>

    Optional: resp="#editorID"

<choice> — Alternative Readings

    Original vs. regularized:

    <choice>
        <orig>IOHN</orig>
        <reg>John</reg>
    </choice>


    Unclear vs. supplied:

    <choice>
        <unclear>Orteli...</unclear>
        <supplied reason="lost">Ortelius</supplied>
    </choice>

<p rend=""> — Column and Layout Control

    Used for two-column page formatting.

    Positions include:
        top, left-top, left-middle, left-bottom,
        right-top, right-middle, right-bottom, bottom.

    Example:
        <p rend="left-top">Text positioned at the top left.</p>

<foreign> — Foreign-Language Text

    Example: <foreign xml:lang="la">DE MVNDO</foreign>

    Declare languages when needed:

        <langUsage>
            <language ident="la" xml:id="lang-lat">Latin</language>
        </langUsage>

<title> — Titles of Works and Maps

    Example:
        <title type="map">Europae Tabula</title>

    Types may include: work, map, book, article.

<personalstmt> — Transcriber Statements

    Example: <personalstmt><!--Transcribed by X--></personalstmt>

<note> — Editorial or Historical Notes

    Examples:
        <note type="editorial" resp="#leblanc">...</note>
        <note type="historical">...</note>

<signature> — Signature Marks

    Example: <signature>xyz</signature>